				 L amp;T joins hands with Raytheon
 OUR CORRESPONDENT																								Mumbai, Nov. 20: Larsen amp; Toubro (L amp;T) has signed an agreement with Raytheon Company of the US to build medium multi-role combat aircraft.																								The deal with the $20-billion US giant will help L amp;T induct state-of-the-art technology. It will expand our range of high value offerings in the defence sector, said M.V. Kotwal, senior executive vice-president (heavy engineering division) at L amp;T.																								While Raytheon has conducted business in India for many years, we are now looking to develop our relationship and presence here in a more meaningful way over the long term, said Wes Motooka, vice-president (international strategy, business development) Raytheon Space and Airborne Systems. 																								Motooka said Raytheons aim was to expand the applications of its technology with the help of best local expertise for the benefit of India.																								The MoU represents a step toward establishing a strong working relationship, encouraging pursuit of emerging business opportunities, and providing for in-country offset for the MMRCA (medium multi-role combat aircraft) programme, L amp;T said in a statement.																								L amp;T has been a major supplier of critical systems to the countrys defence and space research sectors for more than three decades. 
